snippet.textDisplay:
Marcus smart is now a 13 ppg and 5 apg guy who shoots over 35 percent on volume 3s. Wow. That’s so cool. He’s a DPOY fringe candidate basically every year, and now he’s also an effective offensive player. I’m so happy for him. You know something else? People forget how young Marcus still is himself. Not young compared to today’s young stars, but young compared to the mature vibe he gives off and that feeling that he’s been a Celtic for a decade. Dudes 25!! Like..buddy hield. Of course we still think of him as a young player who hasn’t hit his prime yet riggt? Well he’s 2 years older than smart haha. 25!!! Dude looks and acts like a 10 year 33 year old veteran. He could actually become a really good 2 wya player in his prime, as opposed to an amaiNf defender who is solid on offense. I’m talking like 15/5/5/2/1 type guy. And if we look at the trajectory of his shooting, who’s to say it won’t continue and he won’t end up as a 40 percent shooter from deep??

I can’t believe he’s 25 lol.

This celtics team is SO set for the future.
